Azure Storage Account
The Azure storage account Standard general-purpose v2 is the most common type which supports Blob Storage (including Data Lake Storage),
Queue Storage, Table Storage, and Azure Files. Reference: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/storage/common/storage-account-overview

Azure File Sync is a service that allows users to sync files between on-premises and cloud Windows servers.
 Reference: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/storage/file-sync/file-sync-introduction

Azure Storage Account provides access to your Azure storage resources.
Azure Storage Explorer allows you to upload to Azure, download from Azure, or move between storage accounts.
Azure File Sync is a service that allows users to sync files between on-premises and cloud Windows servers.
AzCopy is a CLI tool for copying blobs or files.


Azure Identity
Azure provide identity management system {id/pwd } based on "Active Directory "AD or AAD -> identiy as a service
Azure AD MFA works by requiring two or more of the following authentication methods:
• Something you know, typically a password.
 • Something you have, such as a trusted device that's not easily duplicated, like a phone or hardware key.
  • Something you are - biometrics like a fingerprint or face scan. Reference: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/active-directory/authentication/concept-mfa-howitworks

RBAC -- Role Based Active Control
Roles -- reprsents common tasks for the job
Permissions to that role  -- Users to that role

Azure Active Directory (Azure AD) allows organizations to synchronize on-premises
directories to enable a consistent identity experience between cloud and on-premises.
Reference: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/active-directory/fundamentals/active-directory-whatis

The Microsoft Defender secure score feature in Defender for Cloud enables you to achieve below two main goals:
 • to help you understand your current security situation • to help you efficiently and effectively improve your security


