Azure Arc
Azure ARC allows you to see and manage all of your on premises infrastructure, regardless of where
that infrastructure is running outside of Azure.
And so what that means is you can have servers and Kubernetes clusters and SQL servers that are either
running inside your organization on premises or in other clouds such as Amazon, AWS, and you can see
and manage them all within this AAC dashboard.And so this is basically the consolidation of all your servers running across multiple clouds and in
your own environment

IAAC -Infrastructure as code means all ur vm servers,load balancer and networks all ur configurtaion is stored in
a configuration file ,, ie whta is known as iac and store that file in github or any code repo
U can take that and redploy it when u mess it up

Drift is when u accidentalyy change ur IAC configuration and thru this pervious commit u can get back to the state where it was

IAc option are Arm Templates{json},terraform 3rd part tool to code ur infrastructure,bicep ,chef puppet

What is Arm Templates Azure resource Manager it is service the command line tool that runs underneath ur azure portal
alllows us to interact with resource groups

With Azure Cloud Shell, you can run scripts using Bash or PowerShell.


Monitoring Tools
The Azure Advisor will analyze your use of Azure and make you specific recommendations based on your usage across
reliability (formerly called availability, security, performance, cost and operational excellence categories.
 Reference: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/advisor/advisor-overview

Azure Service Health allows you keep track of Azure resource, both your specifically deployed resources and the overall status of Azure.
 Azure Service Health is composed of Azure status, the service health service, and Resource Health.

Azure Monitor is a comprehensive monitoring solution for Azure services that includes several monitoring tools and services.
You can use Azure Monitor to monitor applications, VMs, containers, DB, security or networking events in Azure, other clouds, or on-premises.

